{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","text":"Overview","level":2,"anchor":"overview"},{"syntax":null,"code":["ðŸ§¬ Theme version: 1.5.0"],"type":"codeListing"},{"type":"heading","text":"Overview","level":2,"anchor":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This is the Orange Business Tools theme any for some business tools products, and cannot be subclassed."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"This theme is related to "},{"code":"OrangeTheme","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" module to use some raw tokens of colors."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Some products may have heavy and very rich user interfaces with a lot of components and elements to displays and","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"with which users can interact. Thus for such products there are specific constraints of spaces and sizes.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"That is the reason why this team is created.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"heading","text":"How to use the theme","level":2,"anchor":"How-to-use-the-theme"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You can use "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesOrangeBusinessTools\/documentation\/OUDSThemesOrangeBusinessTools\/OrangeBusinessToolsTheme","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" directly. To use the "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesOrangeBusinessTools\/documentation\/OUDSThemesOrangeBusinessTools\/OrangeBusinessToolsTheme","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" without further modifications, you will have to use the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"OUDSThemeableView"},{"type":"text","text":" for your root view and give it an instance of "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesOrangeBusinessTools\/documentation\/OUDSThemesOrangeBusinessTools\/OrangeBusinessToolsTheme","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":". Keep in mind the themes are "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"Swift class objects","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" and can be heavy, so you may use only as instance as singleton and not store any properties."}]},{"syntax":"swift","code":["import OUDS \/\/ To get OUDSThemeableView","import OUDSThemesOrangeBusinessTools \/\/ To get OrangeBusinessToolsTheme","import SwiftUI","","@main","struct YourApp: App {","    var body: some Scene {","        WindowGroup {","            OUDSThemeableView(theme: OrangeBusinessToolsTheme()) {","                \/\/ Your root view","            }","        }","    }","}"],"type":"codeListing"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Then, in your views, you can simply use the theme through an environment variable to get the tokens:","type":"text"}]},{"syntax":"swift","code":["import OUDS \/\/ To get the theme environment variable","import SwiftUI","","struct SomeView: View {","","    \/\/ Get OUDS environment variable for theme thanks to themeable view","    @Environment(\\.theme) var theme","    ","    var body: some View {","        ","        \/\/ Use the theme to retrieve the tokens","        \/\/ For spaces: theme.spaces","        \/\/ For sizes: theme.sizes","        \/\/ For borders: theme.borders","        \/\/ For elevations: theme.elevations","        \/\/ For opacities: theme.opacities","        \/\/ For colors: theme.colors","        \/\/ For button configuration: theme.button","        \/\/ For link configuration: theme.link","        \/\/ Etc.","    }","}"],"type":"codeListing"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"This theme embeds and registers the fonts for the Orange Business Tools theme, you just need to use the theme object as is.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"heading","text":"How to enrich the theme","level":2,"anchor":"How-to-enrich-the-theme"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"You cannot derivate the ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"Orange Business Tools","